# This file documents backend (Firebase) configuration
# These values are configured in your Firebase Console, not as environment variables

# Firebase Project Configuration
# ==============================
# These are found in Firebase Console > Project Settings > Service Accounts

# 1. Authentication
# - Enable Google OAuth
#   - Go to Authentication > Sign-in method > Google
#   - Add your domain to authorized redirect URIs (e.g., http://localhost:3000)
#
# - Enable Email/Password
#   - Go to Authentication > Sign-in method > Email/Password
#   - Enable both options

# 2. Firestore Database
# - Create a new Firestore database in production mode
# - Collections to create:
#   - `users` (auto-created on first user signup)
#   - `issues` (auto-created on first issue report)

# 3. Cloud Storage
# - Create a Cloud Storage bucket
# - Set public access rules via Firestore Rules
# - Allow authenticated users to upload files

# 4. Security Rules (Apply in Firestore > Rules)
# See FIRESTORE_SECURITY_RULES.md for complete rules

# 5. Firebase Hosting (Optional)
# - Enable Firebase Hosting
# - Deploy with: firebase deploy --only hosting

# Service Account Setup (for server-side operations)
# ================================================
# Download service account key from Firebase Console:
# - Project Settings > Service Accounts > Generate new private key
# - Save as: serviceAccountKey.json (in .gitignore)
# - Use with Firebase Admin SDK for custom backend operations

# Backup & Recovery
# =================
# Firestore:
# - Automated daily backups available in Firebase Console
# - Manual export via: gcloud firestore export gs://bucket-name/backup

# Storage:
# - Files are automatically versioned
# - Deleted files are in recycle bin for 7 days

# Monitoring
# ==========
# - Firebase Console > Analytics (view user activity)
# - Firebase Console > Performance (monitor app performance)
# - Firebase Console > Crashlytics (view errors)
